WEBVTT

00:02.599 --> 00:06.338
ï»¿Ebola is a highly infectious virus that attacks the internal organs.

00:06.829 --> 00:10.825
Symptoms include fever, weakness, diarrhea, vomiting and bleeding.

00:11.474 --> 00:15.785
The disease is spread through contact with bodily fluids of infected animals and humans.

00:16.352 --> 00:18.925
Fruit bats are considered the natural host of the virus.

00:19.367 --> 00:22.892
Ebola first appeared in the DRC and Sudan in 1976.

00:23.361 --> 00:28.343
Outbreaks occur mainly in rural areas in Central and West Africa in the tropical rainforests.

00:28.779 --> 00:31.348
The current outbreak is the deadliest and the most widespread.

00:32.012 --> 00:36.173
It started in Guinea in March this year and has spread to Sierra Leone and Liberia.

00:36.403 --> 00:40.037
More than 930 people have been killed by the deadly virus...

00:40.223 --> 00:42.009
...and that number continues to rise.

00:42.404 --> 00:46.756
The fatality rate is as high as 90 percent and there is currently no known cure.

